### English Title:
Israeli Army Intercepts Missile Launched from Yemen

### English Text Summary:
The Israeli army announced that its air defenses intercepted a missile launched from Yemen, activating alarms in several areas of the country. The spokesperson for the Israeli army, Avichai Adraee, confirmed the interception on social media. The alarms were triggered across the country following the missile launch. The Iranian-aligned Houthi rebels have been launching drones and ballistic missiles at various locations in Israel in support of Gaza. Meanwhile, the Houthi health ministry claimed that 20 people were killed and 50 injured in American airstrikes on the Ras Issa oil port in Al Hudaydah, Yemen, following reports of these strikes.

